OL,3,CNumber of children 'severely absent'
OL,4,Cfrom school in England 'has become
OL,5,Cendemic'
OL,7,FSchool absences in England have become
OL,8,F"endemic", with government figures
OL,9,Fshowing a significant rise in the
OL,10,Fnumber of pupils missing school for
OL,11,Flong periods.
OL,13,FData from the Department for Education
OL,14,F(DfE) shows 2.1% of pupils were
OL,15,F"severely absent" in the autumn and
OL,16,Fspring terms of 2023/24 in England,
OL,17,Fcompared to 1.9% in the same terms in
OL,18,F2022/23.
