OL,7,FThis is more than double (0.8%) the
OL,8,Fpercentage of pupils who were severely
OL,9,Fabsent ` missing at least half of
OL,10,Fpossible school sessions ` in the
OL,11,Fautumn and spring terms of 2018/19,
OL,12,Fthe academic year before the pandemic.
OL,14,FAround 158,000 pupils were severely
OL,15,Fabsent over the autumn and spring
OL,16,Fterms of 2023/24, compared to 139,000
OL,17,Fover the same period in 2022/23.
