OL,7,FThe data shows that nearly a fifth
OL,8,F(19.2%) of pupils in England - around
OL,9,F1.42 million - were "persistently
OL,10,Fabsent," missing at least 10% of
OL,11,Fschool sessions during autumn and
OL,12,Fspring 2023/24.
OL,14,FThis is down on the same period in
OL,15,F2022/23 when 21.2% of pupils were
OL,16,Fpersistently absent ` but it is still
OL,17,Fabove the rate in the autumn and
OL,18,Fspring terms of 2018/19 (10.5%).
