OL,7,FOverall, the national absence rate has
OL,8,Fdecreased from 7.3% in autumn and
OL,9,Fspring 2022/23 to 6.9% in autumn and
OL,10,Fspring 2023/24, but it remains above
OL,11,Fthe pre-pandemic rate (which was below
OL,12,F5%).
OL,14,FBeth Prescott, programme lead at the
OL,15,FCentre for Social Justice (CSJ), said:
OL,16,F"Four years on from the pandemic and
OL,17,Fschool closures, the crisis of kids
OL,18,Fmissing school shows no sign of
OL,19,Fabating. Severe absence is up year on
OL,20,Fyear, and one in five children remain
OL,21,Fpersistently absent.
